OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLA to pay $20m for beach   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fseized from black family   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Los Angeles has agreed to pay $20m     
OL,6, (#16.7m) for a beach that was seized   
OL,7, from a black family in the 1920s and   
OL,8, returned to their heirs this summer.   
OL,10,FBruce's Beach was purchased in 1912 to 
OL,11,Fcreate a resort for black people at a  
OL,12,Ftime of widespread racial segregation. 
OL,14,FLocated in the desirable city of       
OL,15,FManhattan Beach, it was forcibly taken 
OL,16,Fby the local council in 1924.          
OL,18,FThe Bruce descendants would be rich    
OL,19,Falready if their land was never taken, 
OL,20,Fsaid a LA official announcing the sale.
